CatDescriptText: Roosevelt Smith, laborer, 61 Tannehill Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 21, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the steel strike will be resumed after the 80-day 'cooling-off' period imposed by the Supreme Court under the injection of the Taft-Hartley Act?" answer reads: "I believe that there will be a compromise and a settlement."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Roosevelt Smith wearing dark double breasted pea coat, plaid cap, and striped shirt, standing in front of textured block wall
